From: 
Date: Mon, 14 Jul 2025 00:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] mfd: bcm2835-pm: add BCM2712 watchdog support

Add brcm,bcm2712-pm compatible string to the bcm2835-pm MFD driver and
a corresponding PM/watchdog device-tree node to bcm2712.dtsi.

The mainline bcm2712.dtsi does not include a PM node. The downstream
RPi/RevPi kernels carry this in bcm2712-ds.dtsi with compatible
"brcm,bcm2712-pm". Without this patch the bcm2835-wdt watchdog driver
cannot probe on BCM2712-based boards (Raspberry Pi 5, RevPi Connect 5).

The PM node is placed inside the soc bus at its hardware address
0x7d200000 and exposes the watchdog, power-domain and reset-controller
interfaces used by bcm2835-wdt and, optionally, bcm2835-power.

Signed-off-by: 
---
 drivers/mfd/bcm2835-pm.c                         | 1 +
 arch/arm64/boot/dts/broadcom/bcm2712.dtsi        | 9 +++++++++
 2 files changed, 10 insertions(+)

diff --git a/drivers/mfd/bcm2835-pm.c b/drivers/mfd/bcm2835-pm.c
--- a/drivers/mfd/bcm2835-pm.c
+++ b/drivers/mfd/bcm2835-pm.c
@@ -97,6 +97,7 @@ static const struct of_device_id bcm2835_pm_of_match[] = {
 	{ .compatible = "brcm,bcm2835-pm-wdt", },
 	{ .compatible = "brcm,bcm2835-pm", },
 	{ .compatible = "brcm,bcm2711-pm", },
+	{ .compatible = "brcm,bcm2712-pm", },
 	{},
 };
 MODULE_DEVICE_TABLE(of, bcm2835_pm_of_match);
diff --git a/arch/arm64/boot/dts/broadcom/bcm2712.dtsi b/arch/arm64/boot/dts/broadcom/bcm2712.dtsi
--- a/arch/arm64/boot/dts/broadcom/bcm2712.dtsi
+++ b/arch/arm64/boot/dts/broadcom/bcm2712.dtsi
@@ -167,6 +167,15 @@
 			status = "disabled";
 		};
 
+		pm: watchdog@7d200000 {
+			compatible = "brcm,bcm2712-pm";
+			reg = <0x7d200000 0x308>;
+			reg-names = "pm";
+			#power-domain-cells = <1>;
+			#reset-cells = <1>;
+			system-power-controller;
+		};
+
 		pinctrl: pinctrl@7d504100 {
 			compatible = "brcm,bcm2712c0-pinctrl";
 			reg = <0x7d504100 0x30>;
